<P><HI>"Re&s;olved,</HI> That the Senate will, on next determine on the articles of accu&s;ation and im|peachment exhibited by the Hou&s;e of Repre&s;entatives, again&s;t <HI>John Nichol&s;on,</HI> Comptroller-General of the com|monwealth and that the que&s;tion to be put to each Mem|ber &s;hall be&mdash;"Is <HI>John Nichol&s;on guilty</HI> or <HI>not guilty</HI> of high mi&s;demeanors charged upon him by the Hou&s;e of Repre&s;entatives?" The an&s;wer &s;hall be general if <HI>not guilty,</HI> but if <HI>guilty,</HI> &s;hall &s;pecify on what article or ar|ticles he is <HI>guilty.</HI></P>
